node.title: Victoria records 941 new local COVID-19 cases and eight deaths, new tier 1 exposure sites listed
node.alt: A resident receives a dose of the Pfizer Covid-19 vaccine in Australia's first drive through vaccination centre
node.description: There are now 18,361 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 326 people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 941\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and eight\u00a0deaths.", "It is the second day in a row the state has recorded fewer than 1,000 new cases.", "There are now 18,361\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 326\u00a0people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.", "The new cases were detected from 63,278\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There are 657\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 117\u00a0are in intensive care\u00a0and 69\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "There were 9,440\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, and more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "
New tier 1 exposure sites listed
", "Health authorities have listed more tier 1 COVID-19 exposure sites in Victoria.", "The new tier 1 sites are:", "Anyone who has been to a tier 1 exposure site at the specified time\u00a0must get tested and isolate for 14 days if unvaccinated, or for seven days if fully vaccinated.", "Check the list below for all of the exposure sites and times.", "You can find information on testing site hours and your\u00a0nearest site on the Department of Health\u00a0website.", "", "
